CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper September 26, 1959, pg. B2, reads: "In Celebration of Pittsburgh's Bicentennial - Pa. Training School Marks 'Pioneer Day' - What're They Doin'? - When students at the Pennsylvania Training School celebrated 'Pioneer Day' last Saturday, they performed all sorts of stunts. Here they resort to the old original way of cleaning up a plate full of grub. Guess who won? The girls! - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Young men and women participating in eating contest with Johnny Morton wearing striped jacket on right, for "Pioneer Day" celebration at Pennsylvania Training School, Canonsburg
